'''九型人格學（{{Lang-en|Enneagram}}）'''是一個關於人類個性的模型，一般把其理解為一套把人類劃分為九種相互關聯的（非心理学的）人格的類型學，[[九角星|九角星]]的每一点在九型人格學中代表每一种人格<ref name="Ellis">{{cite book|last1=Ellis|first1=Albert |authorlink1=Albert Ellis (psychologist)|last2=Abrams|first2=Mike |last3=Dengelegi Abrams|first3=Lidia |title=Personality theories: critical perspectives|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4_FOIKi2_tYC&pg=PA569&lpg=PA569&dq=%22New+age+theories+of+personality:+The+Enneagram%22#v=onepage&q=%22New%20age%20theories%20of%20personality%3A%20The%20Enneagram%22&f=false|year=2008|publisher=SAGE|isbn=978-1-4129-7062-4|quote=Ichazo has disowned Naranjo, Palmer and the other Jesuit writers on the Enneagram on the grounds that his descriptions of the nine types represent ego fixations that develop in early childhood in response to trauma.}}</ref>。其被認為類型之間的存有一些不同的連接。

对于九型人格的具体研究中[[心理统计学|心理统计与计量学]]分析非常有限，其领域同行评审研究尚未在相关心理学学术团体中广泛接受和承认，其理论无法被证伪，不具有科学性，被认为并非是真正的[[人格心理学|人格]]与[[心理学|心理科学]]，而更多的被[[心理学|心理学]]界认为是[[伪科学|伪科学]]（Pseudoscience）<ref name="Thyer">{{cite book|last1=Thyer|first1=Bruce A|last2=Pignotti|first2=Monica|title=Science and Pseudoscience in Social Work Practice|url=https://books.google.nl/books?hl=zh-CN&lr=&id=EQFPCQAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PP1&dq=Science+and+Pseudoscience+in+Social+Work+Practice&ots=ACyQLUCaEh&sig=OgYCdF8eToPRxMO93UmBV39FZOU&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=Science%20and%20Pseudoscience%20in%20Social%20Work%20Practice&f=false|year=2015|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-0-8261-7768-1|access-date=2019-11-07|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820045343/https://books.google.nl/books?hl=zh-CN&lr=&id=EQFPCQAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PP1&dq=Science+and+Pseudoscience+in+Social+Work+Practice&ots=ACyQLUCaEh&sig=OgYCdF8eToPRxMO93UmBV39FZOU&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=Science%20and%20Pseudoscience%20in%20Social%20Work%20Practice&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在商業環境中，九型人格學通常用作分类及深入了解每位員工的性格及大体的工作环境；在靈性上，它更常作為一種通往更高的存在、精神和啟蒙狀態的途徑 ，它被描述為一種自我理解和自我發展的方法<ref name="Clarke" />。通過研討會、會議、書籍、雜誌和DVD的推广，九型人格學在商業管理和精神語境中都得到广泛的應用<ref name="Clarke">{{cite book|last1=Clarke|first1=Peter |title=Encyclopedia of new religious movements|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KLipBC05pF8C&pg|year=2004|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=0-203-48433-9}}</ref><ref name="Kemp">{{cite book|last=Kemp|first=Daren|title=New age: a guide : alternative spiritualities from Aquarian conspiracy to Next Age|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xz4EWg1WWmMC&pg=PA80&dq=%22New+age%22+%22Enneagram%22#v=onepage&q=%22Enneagram%22&f=false|year=2004|publisher=Edinburgh University Press|isbn=978-0-7486-1532-2|access-date=2017-02-14|archive-date=2017-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170217092818/https://books.google.com/books?id=xz4EWg1WWmMC&pg=PA80&dq=%22New+age%22+%22Enneagram%22#v=onepage&q=%22Enneagram%22&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

雖然九型人格學的想法和理論之歷史存有很大的爭議空間，但當代的理論主要來自智利的心理學家{{link-en|奧斯卡·伊茲查洛|Oscar Ichazo}}和{{tsl|en|Claudio Naranjo|克勞帝歐·那朗荷}}。那朗荷的理論部分是受到[[喬治·伊凡諾維奇·葛吉夫|葛吉夫]]這位導師的影響。九型人格學的導師亦因思想不同，而令他們理論上的一些意念並不總是一致<ref name="Ellis" />。

